Re: Possible claim for excess proceeds from an Ohio tax foreclosure or forfeited land sale

Dear {{ owner_name or "Property Owner" }},

Our records indicate that property associated with {{ county_name }} County, Ohio may have generated excess proceeds after a tax foreclosure or forfeited land sale. Under Ohio Revised Code § 5721.19 (judicial tax sales) and § 5723 (forfeited land sales), excess proceeds are the funds that remain after the county applies sale proceeds to delinquent taxes, penalties, costs, and other amounts allowed by law. These funds are held by the County Treasurer until claimed.

